text: Bugaldie is a locality in north-western New South Wales, Australia. A railway station on the now closed Gwabegar railway line was located there between 1923 and 1976.Bugaldie station NSWrail.net, accessed 9 April 2010. ==Population== In the 2016 Census, there were 144 people in Bugaldie. 80.6% of people were born in Australia and 96.4% of people spoke only English at home.50px Material was copied from this source, which is available under a Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License. ==References== Category:Localities in New South Wales Category:Warrumbungle Shire
